const headHtml = "<title>Gemstone Mining Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock</title>\n    <meta name=\"description\" content=\"An expert based gemstone mining guide explaining pristine breakpoints, powder, route quality, competition and when gemstone mining actually outperforms easier mining routes.\">\n    <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/gemstone-mining-guide\">\n\n    <meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/gemstone-mining-guide\">\n    <meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\">\n    <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Gemstone Mining Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock\">\n    <meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Learn when gemstone mining is worth the setup: powder, pristine, route control and live pricing all matter more than flashy showcase numbers.\">\n    <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/static/NEC.png\">\n    <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n      {\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"Gemstone Mining Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock\",\"description\":\"Expert based gemstone mining guide focused on setup quality, route control and gemstone ROI in Hypixel SkyBlock.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-03-16\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-04-18\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NotEnoughCoins\"},\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Coflnet GmbH\"},\"url\":\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/gemstone-mining-guide\"}\n    </script>";
const bodyHtml = "<main>\n      <div class=\"site-shell article-layout\">\n        <article class=\"article\">\n          <a class=\"article-meta\" href=\"/guides#months-list\">2026-03-16 • Mining</a>\n          <h1>Gemstone Mining Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock</h1>\n          <p class=\"lede\">Gemstone mining is the route every ambitious mining player eventually compares themselves against, and for good reason: at strong setup levels it can still produce serious income. But the biggest lesson from current mining creator coverage is that gemstone mining is far more setup-sensitive than casual viewers expect. The route only becomes impressive when several systems align at the same time: powder, pristine, route quality, equipment quality and the ability to avoid downtime. Remove any one of those and the headline number collapses quickly.</p>\n          <div class=\"note\"><strong>Primary source base:</strong> Candypat's mining comparison coverage plus the Divan-versus-Glossy discussion that shows how powder and gear gates reshape gemstone claims.</div>\n          <h2>Gemstone mining is a system, not just a pickaxe choice</h2>\n          <p>Players who fail with gemstones usually focus too narrowly on the visible gear. They ask whether one drill is enough, whether a specific armor tier is mandatory or whether a reforge alone will unlock the method. In practice, gemstone income is a stack of small efficiencies. Pristine matters, but so do the surrounding mining stats. Powder matters, but so does whether your route is actually clean enough to express the stats you paid for. Even the best gear struggles to rescue a bad route full of travel waste or player competition.</p>\n          <p>This is why the Divan versus Glossy discussion matters. It is not just a flex comparison. It represents the broader question of whether your account is at the stage where gemstone mining should be a main money method or a future target. The stronger your setup gets, the more gemstone mining starts to resemble a precision machine. Before that point, it often behaves like an expensive promise that has not been fully activated yet.</p>\n          <h2>Competition and route control are real costs</h2>\n          <p>One weakness of simplistic gemstone guides is that they treat the route as if it exists in a vacuum. It does not. Public routes attract competition, and crowded routes drag real profits down even when the theoretical setup is perfect. That is why practical gemstone advice always sounds more conservative than showcase content. A route that looks weaker on paper but stays uncontested can outperform a famous route you keep sharing with three other miners.</p>\n          <p>Use the live tools to monitor gemstone-related price shifts in real time. <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/topMovers\">SkyCofl top movers</a> catches powder, gem and Divan-related swings as they happen, <a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/\">Skyblock.bz</a> ranks gemstone products by 24h movement, <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/margin\">BazaarTracker margin</a> shows you spread depth, and <a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/converters\">BazaarPro converters</a> covers gem-to-block conversion edges. Live pricing is only half of the equation. Gemstone mining does not forgive poor execution. The market can support the route and you can still underperform if your pathing and uptime are weak.</p>\n          <h2>Read next</h2>\n          <ul class=\"related-list\">\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/mining-money-making-guide-2026\">Best Mining Money-Making Methods in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/sludge-mining-guide\">Sludge Mining Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/first-50m-coins-guide\">Your First 50M Coins in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n        <aside class=\"article-aside\">\n          <div><h3>Best paired tools</h3><ul class=\"tool-list\"><li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/topMovers\">SkyCofl top movers</a></li><li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/forge\">SkyCofl forge flips</a></li><li><a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/\">Skyblock.bz trends</a></li><li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/converters\">BazaarPro converters</a></li><li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/craft-forge-flips\">BazaarPro craft &amp; forge flips</a></li><li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/margin\">BazaarTracker margin</a></li></ul></div>\n          <div><h3>Best for</h3><p>Players deciding whether they have the powder and gear to make gemstones a primary money method.</p></div>\n          <div><h3>Source videos</h3><p>Candypat's comparison framing is the main reference here because it exposes how different gemstone setups fall apart once route and gear assumptions change.</p></div>\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n    </main>";
